          ItemBox[
           PaneBox[
            
            StyleBox["\<\"FindPfaffianSystemBasis[HypSeries, SumVar, Vars, \
Basis] is the same as FindPfaffianSystem[], except that the basis of \
derivatives is supplied by the user as the fourth argument Basis rather than \
constructed automatically.\\nHypSeries is a hypergeometric series given in \
terms of Pochhammer functions.\\nSumVar is the list of summation indices \
appearing in HypSeries:\\n  \[Bullet] {m, n, ...}\\nVars is the list of \
kinematic variables:\\n  \[Bullet] {x, y, ...}\\nBasis is the user-supplied \
list of basis elements (derivatives of the unknown function F):\\n  \[Bullet] \
{F[x,y], Derivative[0,1][F][x,y], Derivative[1,0][F][x,y], \
Derivative[1,1][F][x,y], ...}\\nThe result is the 4-tuple {HypSeries, SumVar, \
Pfaffian, Basis} in the input format expected by \
TransportDE[].\\nExamples:\\n  FindPfaffianSystemBasis[Pochhammer[a,m+n] \
Pochhammer[b,m] Pochhammer[b',n] / (Pochhammer[c,m+n] m! n!) x^m y^n,\\n      \
                    {m, n}, {x, y}, {F[x,y], Derivative[0,1][F][x,y], \
Derivative[1,0][F][x,y], Derivative[1,1][F][x,y]}]\"\>", 
             "InformationUsageText",
